The '''BloodScars''' were a [[Pirate/Legends|pirate]] organization active in [[Shelsha sector/Legends|Shelsha sector]], headed by a [[Human/Legends|Human]] called "[[The Commodore]]" based on [[Gepparin]]. Governor [[Barshnis Choard]] secretly funded the group in hopes that the sector might secede from the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]]; though his plot was foiled by [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]]. Around [[0 ABY/Legends|0.5 ABY]], they tried to branch out to become more powerful, including starting a [[Swoop gang/Legends|swoop gang]] on [[Drunost]] to seize [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] arms, and funding a corrupt police regime in [[Janusar]] on [[Ranklinge]], possibly to try to steal [[I-7 Howlrunner]]s from a nearby plant. Their most audacious move was an attempt, foiled by Jade, to steal a transport carrying 50 [[All Terrain Scout Transport/Legends|AT-STs]]. Disra tried to recruit them for his scheme to defeat the Rebellion in Shelsa Sector. The plan failed and both the Commodore and [[Caaldra]] were killed and the [[BloodScar base|base]] on Gepparin [[Bombing of Gepparin|destroyed]] by the [[Star Destroyer/Legends|Star Destroyer]] [[Reprisal (Imperial II-class)|''Reprisal'']].

The BloodScars once staged a raid near [[Ashkas-kov]]. In this episode, the BloodScars attacked an entire convoy with ten of their own ships, and even blew up the four ships they had primarily targeted after stripping them of goods.

